            <h2>Common Legal Issues for Richmond Hill Chinese-Canadian Families</h2>
            <p>Richmond Hill family law cases often involve high-value home division, disputes over children's school choices, and cross-border asset transfers. Miao He has extensive experience with these matters.</p>
            <p><strong>Property division:</strong> Ontario's Family Law Act requires Equalization of net family property accumulated during the marriage — this includes homes, investment accounts, and pensions. Miao He helps clients accurately calculate their Net Family Property and protect assets that should be excluded, such as pre-marital property and parental gifts.</p>
            <p><strong>Child custody and parenting:</strong> Richmond Hill Chinese-Canadian families often disagree on which school children should attend, whether children can travel to China to visit grandparents, and how Chinese cultural education fits into parenting plans. Miao He drafts detailed Parenting Plans that address these real-world issues with legal enforceability.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h2>Marriage Contracts in Richmond Hill</h2>
            <p>Demand for marriage contracts is high in Richmond Hill — particularly in cases involving parental down payments, family trust assets, and inherited or pre-immigration property. Miao He provides full Chinese-language drafting and legal advice, ensuring the contract meets Ontario court standards and will not be set aside for unfairness.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h2>Emergency Motions &amp; Asset Protection</h2>
            <p>If you suspect a spouse is transferring or hiding assets, or if there is a risk of children being removed from Ontario, Miao He can move quickly to obtain a temporary restraining order or Mareva Injunction to protect your interests.</p>
          </div>

